         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Open Invitation to Tender for the provision of Rochdale &amp; Oldham Collaborative Substance Misuse Treatment &amp; Recovery Service</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN280497</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="85000000"/>
               <CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="AA01"/>
               <CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="AA01"/>
               <CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="AA01"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Oldham &amp; Rochdale Councils have agreed to join together and tender for the new Drug and Alcohol service.</P>
               <P>The overall aim of the new joint treatment system is to deliver an integrated recovery-orientated treatment system with two town center treatment delivery sites, some shared facilities, and some localized provision (including primary care) in order to meet demand.</P>
               <P>The system should reduce the risk of harm and support people in the two boroughs to maintain long-term recovery from their addiction, ensuring that the service users are at the center of delivery with other services wrapped around them.</P>
               <P>The initial contract value is £13.2m for 3 years (plus options to extend for up to 2 years on an annual basis). The contract value shown at II.1.5 exceeds the available budget and is an approximate value in recognition of the possibility that other councils may join the contract at a later stage.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">22000000</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85000000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="98000000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>This is a competitive procurement in accordance with the Open Procedure under EU Procurement Directives and implemented in English Law in the Public Contract Regulations 2015 (SI 2015 No.102) and such other UK regulations implementing its provisions as may be made from time to time. Oldham Council intends to award a single contract covering the provision of the service across both Local Authorities.</P>
                  <P>Oldham &amp; Rochdale Councils have agreed to join together and tender for the new Drug and Alcohol service. The overall aim of the new joint treatment system is to deliver an integrated recovery-orientated treatment system with two town center treatment delivery sites, some shared facilities, and some localized provision (including primary care) in order to meet demand.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Technical Capacity</AC_CRITERION>
